sub_title: A petroleum engineer. Qualifications, skills and experiences in Engineering, Administration, Economics and Computer
summary:
Bachelor of Oil and Gas Engineering - University of Aden - 2015

Qualifications, Skills and Experience in Sciences of Engineering, Administration, Economics, Relief, Safety and Computer. 

Yes, I am a petroleum engineer, but I have many qualifications, skills and experience, most of my Previous experience in volunteer and service works. I have a nice experience in self-learning from my undergraduate until today. I have great enthusiasm for work and I'm ready to training and experimental work period.


The most important personal skills:
1.	 Self-learning skills
2.	 Skills of Leadership and teamwork spirit
3.	 Skills of Time management and Business Scheduling
4.	 communication skills
5.	 Critical Thinking skills
6.	 Strategic Planning skills

The most important academic skills:
1. English language skills: listening, speaking, reading and writing
2. Computer Skills: Office Software, Statistical Software, Geographic Information Systems GIS
3. Internet search skills
4.	 Data entry and fast typing
5. Skills of writing reports and messages.
